  <title type="html"><![CDATA[Homework 4: Probability Theory and Data Visualization]]></title>
  <link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="http:/IDS2020F/homework/4-probability-visualization"/>
  <id>http:/IDS2020F/homework/4-probability-visualization</id>
  <published>2020-11-15T00:00:00-06:00</published>
  <updated>2020-11-15T00:00:00-06:00</updated>
  <author>
    <name>Amir Shahmoradi</name>
    <uri>http:/IDS2020F</uri>
    <email>shahmoradi@utexas.edu</email>
  </author>
  
  <content type="html">
  
    &lt;p&gt;♣ &lt;strong&gt;Due Date: Wednesday Dec 2, 2020 4:00 PM (extended due to Thanksgiving break)&lt;/strong&gt;. This homework aims at giving you some experience with probability theory, and data visualization techniques.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ol&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;
    &lt;p&gt;Name the two major types of uncertainty and explain which one(s) describe the type of uncertainty in Bayesian school of thought.&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;
    &lt;p&gt;Name the most naturally-occurring distribution in Nature.&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;
    &lt;p&gt;What is the probability of obtaining a value 1 and 2 in a single experiment of throwing a die?&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;
    &lt;p&gt;What is the probability of obtaining a value 1 or 2 or larger than 5 in a single experiment of throwing a die?&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;
    &lt;p&gt;What distribution best describes the number of flowers per square feet of a garden, uniformly but randomly distributed across the entire garden?&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;
    &lt;p&gt;Does correlation mean causation? Explain with an example.&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;
    &lt;p&gt;Does correlation between two variables imply dependence between the two variables? Explain with an example.&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;
    &lt;p&gt;what are &lt;em&gt;aesthetics&lt;/em&gt; in data visualization? Name a few aesthetics that can appear in a data visualization.&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;
    &lt;p&gt;Name the two major classes of aesthetics.&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;
    &lt;p&gt;Name the two major types of data and provide an example for each category.&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;
    &lt;p&gt;What is the common name for variables holding qualitative data?&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;
    &lt;p&gt;Provide examples of &lt;em&gt;ordered&lt;/em&gt; and &lt;em&gt;unordered&lt;/em&gt; data.&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;
    &lt;p&gt;What kinds of axes in a plot should be represented with the same units and grid size?&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;
    &lt;p&gt;Describe an example scenario in which transforming the axes of the plot results in better visualizations.&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;
    &lt;p&gt;What kind of data set can be best visualized in &lt;em&gt;polar coordinates&lt;/em&gt;?&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;
    &lt;p&gt;Name four different color scales and explain their most appropriate usage.&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;What is wrong with the following visualization?
    &lt;figure&gt;
    &lt;img src=&quot;./4/wrong.png&quot; alt=&quot;wrong&quot; style=&quot;width:80%&quot; /&gt;
&lt;/figure&gt;
  &lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;
    &lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.cdslab.org/recipes/programming/coordinates-transformation/coordinates-transformation&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Coordinates transformation in visualization&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;/li&gt;
  &lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.cdslab.org/recipes/programming/visualization-coloring/visualization-coloring&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;&gt;Best visualization coloring&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;


  
